parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false trunk sensor alert can cause a distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents, and may also lead to unnecessary stops or investigations.
symptoms: The trunk sensor alerts the driver that the trunk is open when it is actually closed
interior lights turn on
and the alert is triggered when driving with windows down
especially when making turns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, and may also lead to a loss of critical systems, such as lights and safety features.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start
multiple lights blink on the dashboard
the push-start button is unresponsive
and the issue is intermittent and unpredictable.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Drain and Alternator Charging Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drain and alternator charging issues can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, and may also lead to a loss of critical systems, such as lights and safety features.
symptoms: The vehicle's battery fails to start the engine
the battery drains rapidly when the vehicle is not running
and the alternator may not be adequately recharging the battery.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The power door issues can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to accidents or injuries if the doors malfunction while in use.
symptoms: The power doors make a popping sound when opening with the outside handles
and the issue is intermittent and unpredictable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door cable system can cause the door to become inoperable, creating a hazard in emergency situations where passengers need to exit the vehicle quickly.
symptoms: The sliding door will not open
the door cable system breaks
the door becomes inoperable electronically or manually.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the spare tire hold-down cable can cause the cable to fail, leading to the spare tire falling off while driving, which can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The spare tire hold-down cable corrodes
the spare tire falls off while driving
the temporary fix is to store the spare tire inside the vehicle
which takes up valuable space.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The weak design of the hood can cause it to bend or deform easily, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle and increase the risk of injury in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The hood bends or deforms easily
the hood is damaged when the rod supporting it is not removed
the hood is weak and prone to damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, particularly when the vehicle is in a stationary or slow-moving condition.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates on its own
the engine revs loudly
the vehicle lunges forward
the vehicle moves forward despite pressing the brake pedal
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly when shifting into gear.
